friendly_name.description: The string that you assigned to describe the resource.

limits.description: An object that describes the limits of the service instance. The `limits` object contains  `channel_members` to describe the members/channel limit and `user_channels` to describe the channels/user limit. `channel_members` can be 1,000 or less, with a default of 250. `user_channels` can be 1,000 or less, with a default value of 100.

links.description: The absolute URLs of the Service's [Channels](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/api/channels), [Roles](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/api/roles), and [Users](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/api/users).

post_webhook_url.description: The URL for post-event webhooks, which are called by using the `webhook_method`. See [Webhook Events](https://www.twilio.com/docs/api/chat/webhooks) for more details.

pre_webhook_url.description: The URL for pre-event webhooks, which are called by using the `webhook_method`. See [Webhook Events](https://www.twilio.com/docs/api/chat/webhooks) for more details.

reachability_enabled.description: Whether the [Reachability Indicator](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/reachability-indicator) is enabled for this Service instance. The default is `false`.

sid.description: The unique string that we created to identify the Service resource.

typing_indicator_timeout.description: How long in seconds after a `started typing` event until clients should assume that user is no longer typing, even if no `ended typing` message was received.  The default is 5 seconds.

url.description: The absolute URL of the Service resource.

webhook_filters.description: The list of WebHook events that are enabled for this Service instance. See [Webhook Events](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/webhook-events) for more details.

webhook_method.description: The HTTP method to use for calls to the `pre_webhook_url` and `post_webhook_url` webhooks.  Can be: `POST` or `GET` and the default is `POST`. See [Webhook Events](https://www.twilio.com/docs/chat/webhook-events) for more details.

webhooks.description: An object that contains information about the webhooks configured for this service.
